  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Current or Former Smokers with &gt;20 pack year history and or family history of lung cancer.
        Ages 50-75 years old
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        -  Persons 50-75

          -  Asymptomatic for lung cancer

          -  Current or former (stopped smoking less than 10 years ago) cigarette smokers

          -  History of cigarette smoking of at least 20 pack years

          -  History of cigarette smoking with a family history of lung cancer which gives an
             individual a personal risk similar to a smoking history of 20 pk/years (i.e. 1% at 5
             years).

          -  Mentally competent individuals to sign an informed consent.

          -  Healthy enough to undergo pulmonary resection or stereotactic body radiotherapy.

          -  A fully informed signed consent form must have been obtained.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
